properties.documentation: The ARAM Business Layer provides a business view of the automotive system by describing the involved business actors as well as their interest in the system under development. This layer serves as a starting point for the conceptualization of a system.
The ARAM Communication Layer gives an overview of the used protocols and mechanisms between different components of the automotive system.
The ARAM Component Layer provides a high-level physical architecture of the system under development. This architecture outlines a first draft of the system to be developed.
The ARAM Function Layer provides a functional view of the system. It is used to identify functions and services that must be covered by the system.
The ARAM Information Layer describes data that is exchanged between functions, services, or components.
